title: For Sale:  FN FAL .308 Match - Original Belgium / Styer Import - Pre ban model 50.00
postcontent:
FN FAL 50.00 / type II receiver Early 1970‚Äôs
Fabrique Nationale Herstal Belgique
Styer Secaucus N.J.

Unfired - MINT Conditon

Includes (2) Factory Mags

Price Firm - $4000
NO TRADES

Very RARE 
Get one while you still can...

Info on model 50.00
http://www.falfiles.com/forums/showthread.php?t=204747
‚ÄúFollowing the completion of the importation of the 1,848 G Series FAL‚Äôs Browning began the importation of a new Type II receivered FN model 50.00 FAL. Early examples of these FAL‚Äôs featured a standard FN serial number (typically 5 numbers -14XXX)) stamped at the rear of the upper receiver on the LH side and also a 'newly' introduced FN commercial serial numbering system for use on all commercial semi-auto FAL‚Äôs entering the U.S.A. destined for civilian sale that utilized new a 250 prefix. Later Type II examples imported utilized the 250 prefix serial number only. Many collectors will also refer to these FAL's as 'Competition Models'. The 250XXXX prefix number can typically be found on the RH side of the upper receiver to the rear of the ejection port. The bolt and bolt carrier on these dual numbered FAL‚Äôs corresponds to the 5 digit serial number on the LH side of the upper receiver and not the newly incorporated 250 prefix number. All of the examples that I have seen are model 50.00's with fiberglass non-bipod cut handguards and the fluted Browning 'Match' type flash-hider. At some point during the importation of the Type II receivered FAL‚Äôs FN elected to change their preferred U.S.A. importer from Browning to Steyr. During this transitional period of time there were some Type II receivered FAL's imported that featured both Browning Arms and Steyr import markings. I have also seen some Type II FAL's that featured dual Browning Arms and EJK-Devco markings. Given that Type II receivered importation most probably began no earlier than serial number 2500001 and the earliest documented Type III serial number available is 2500743 it is my belief that there can be no more that 742 total examples of this variant imported by Browning and/or Steyr and/or EJK-Devco. When added together with the Browning import Rogak contract Type II receivered FAL‚Äôs one can assume that there were no more than 942 semi-auto Type II receivered FAL‚Äôs imported into the U.S.A. for civilian sales. Given the information available it is clear that there were fewer FN manufactured FAL's imported with Type II receivers that either the earlier Type I's or later Type III's.‚Äù
My understand is less than 200 of the double serial # & double import stamped Browning / Styer type II receviered 50.00 marked FAL‚Äôs where imported & few than that still exist today
